<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="argentinica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea argentinica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and similar species in having leaves abaxially white-tomentose. It is close to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Argyreia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="megapotamica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. megapotamica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the sepals often with a dark gland near the base, but differs in the tomentose leaves and longer sepals, which are about 10 mm in length.
</paragraph>
